{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MDJtdTp51qyoaFgxC1GVJ5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n2\t# Task: lifecycle\n3\t\n4\t## Goal\n5\t\n6\tIn-memory user store and token-based authentication handler for the IAM listener.\n7\t\n8\tEndpoints:\n9\tPOST /users {\"username\":string,\"password\":string} ‚Üí 201 {\"id\":string,\"username\":string} or 400;\n10\tGET /users/{id} ‚Üí 200 {\"id\":string,\"username\":string} or 404;\n11\tDELETE /users/{id} ‚Üí 200 or 404;\n12\tPOST /auth/login {\"username\":string,\"password\":string} ‚Üí 200 {\"token\":string} or 401;\n13\tPOST /auth/logout header Authorization:Bearer <token> ‚Üí 200 or 401.\n14\t\n15\tIn-memory stores: UserStore map[id]‚Üí{id string, username string, passwordHash string}, TokenStore map[token]‚ÜíuserID string. IDs generated with crypto/rand or math/rand UUID. Passwords hashed with bcrypt or sha256. Exposes an http.Handler (or *http.ServeMux) for registration by integrate-iam.\n16\t\n17\t## Context\n18\t\n19\t### Level 1 ‚Äî fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n20\t\n21\t### Level 2 ‚Äî fbc6d9-0001-iam\n22\tIdentity and access management listener (port 8082) composed of two sub-components ‚Äî lifecycle (user CRUD and authentication) and authz-rbac (roles and permission checks) ‚Äî that together handle all ten IAM HTTP endpoints.\n23\t\n24\t## Components\n25\t\n26\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n27\t\n28\t## Design\n29\t\n30\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n31\t\n32\t## Acceptance Criteria\n33\t\n34\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n35\t\n36\t## Test Command\n37\t\n38\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n39\t\n40\t## Suggested Tools\n41\t\n42\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n43\t\n44\t## Notes\n45\t\n46\t_None._\n47\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"1d19e7e9-5705-4d5e-a6b7-f42170180c07","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:11:53.714Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/target/project/tasks/main/in-progress/fbc6d9-platform/fbc6d9-0000-build-1/fbc6d9-0001-iam/fbc6d9-0000-lifecycle/README.md","content":"<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n# Task: lifecycle\n\n## Goal\n\nIn-memory user store and token-based authentication handler for the IAM listener.\n\nEndpoints:\nPOST /users {\"username\":string,\"password\":string} ‚Üí 201 {\"id\":string,\"username\":string} or 400;\nGET /users/{id} ‚Üí 200 {\"id\":string,\"username\":string} or 404;\nDELETE /users/{id} ‚Üí 200 or 404;\nPOST /auth/login {\"username\":string,\"password\":string} ‚Üí 200 {\"token\":string} or 401;\nPOST /auth/logout header Authorization:Bearer <token> ‚Üí 200 or 401.\n\nIn-memory stores: UserStore map[id]‚Üí{id string, username string, passwordHash string}, TokenStore map[token]‚ÜíuserID string. IDs generated with crypto/rand or math/rand UUID. Passwords hashed with bcrypt or sha256. Exposes an http.Handler (or *http.ServeMux) for registration by integrate-iam.\n\n## Context\n\n### Level 1 ‚Äî fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n\n### Level 2 ‚Äî fbc6d9-0001-iam\nIdentity and access management listener (port 8082) composed of two sub-components ‚Äî lifecycle (user CRUD and authentication) and authz-rbac (roles and permission checks) ‚Äî that together handle all ten IAM HTTP endpoints.\n\n## Components\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Design\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Test Command\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Suggested Tools\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Notes\n\n_None._\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}}}
