{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015HjLsgsr3CZXoqKGLnF9n1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Acceptance Spec\n2\t<!-- Generated by ACCEPTANCE_SPEC_WRITER. Do not edit manually. -->\n3\t\n4\t**Metrics listener (port 8081)**\n5\t\n6\tRecords frontend user interaction events.\n7\t\n8\tAPI:\n9\t- `POST /events` ‚Äî record an event; body: `{\"type\": \"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\", \"userId\": \"<string>\", \"payload\": {}}` ‚Üí 201 with event object (includes generated `id`)\n10\t- `GET /events`  ‚Äî list all recorded events ‚Üí 200 with JSON array\n11\t\n12\t**IAM listener (port 8082)**\n13\t\n14\tIdentity and access management. Internally composed of two logical components:\n15\t(a) user authentication and lifecycle, and (b) authorisation/RBAC.\n16\t\n17\tAPI:\n18\t- User lifecycle:\n19\t  - `POST /users`        ‚Äî register user; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` ‚Üí 201 with user object (includes `id`, no password in response)\n20\t  - `GET /users/{id}`    ‚Äî get user by ID ‚Üí 200 or 404\n21\t  - `DELETE /users/{id}` ‚Äî delete user ‚Üí 200/204 or 404\n22\t- Authentication:\n23\t  - `POST /auth/login`   ‚Äî authenticate; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` ‚Üí 200 with token object (includes `token` field)\n24\t  - `POST /auth/logout`  ‚Äî invalidate token; header: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` ‚Üí 200/204\n25\t- RBAC:\n26\t  - `POST /roles`             ‚Äî create role; body: `{\"name\": \"<string>\", \"permissions\": [\"<string>\"]}` ‚Üí 201 with role object (includes `id`)\n27\t  - `GET /roles`              ‚Äî list roles ‚Üí 200 with JSON array\n28\t  - `POST /users/{id}/roles`  ‚Äî assign role to user; body: `{\"roleId\": \"<string>\"}` ‚Üí 200/201\n29\t  - `GET /users/{id}/roles`   ‚Äî list user's roles ‚Üí 200 with JSON array\n30\t  - `POST /authz/check`       ‚Äî check permission; body: `{\"userId\": \"<string>\", \"permission\": \"<string>\"}` ‚Üí 200 