{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014TCm9UweYVZr2RrvNMLW5D","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# metrics\n2\t\n3\tPurpose: Describes the design of the in-memory metrics package that records and lists frontend user interaction events.\n4\tExposes two HTTP endpoints on port 8081, implemented as a reusable `http.Handler` returned by `routes.go`.\n5\t\n6\tTags: architecture, design\n7\t\n8\t## File Index\n9\t\n10\t| File | Description |\n11\t|------|-------------|\n12\t| `store.go` | `EventStore` ‚Äî thread-safe in-memory slice of `Event` records with `Add` and `List` methods |\n13\t| `handlers.go` | `PostEvent` and `GetEvents` ‚Äî `http.HandlerFunc` factories wired to an `EventStore` |\n14\t| `routes.go` | `NewRouter` ‚Äî assembles and returns the `http.Handler` for the metrics service |\n15\t| `store_test.go` | Unit tests for `EventStore.Add` and `EventStore.List` |\n16\t| `handlers_test.go` | Unit tests for `PostEvent` and `GetEvents` using `net/http/httptest` |\n17\t\n18\t## Overview\n19\t\n20\t### Data model\n21\t\n22\t```go\n23\ttype Event struct {\n24\t    ID      string                 `json:\"id\"`\n25\t    Type    string                 `json:\"type\"`\n26\t    UserID  string                 `json:\"userId\"`\n27\t    Payload map[string]interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n28\t}\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\tField names match the spec verbatim (`id`, `type`, `userId`, `payload`).\n32\t\n33\t### EventStore (`store.go`)\n34\t\n35\t```go\n36\ttype EventStore struct {\n37\t    mu     sync.RWMutex\n38\t    events []Event\n39\t}\n40\t\n41\tfunc NewEventStore() *EventStore\n42\tfunc (s *EventStore) Add(e Event) Event   // caller supplies all fields except ID; Add assigns UUID and appends\n43\tfunc (s *EventStore) List() []Event       // returns a shallow copy; never returns nil\n44\t```\n45\t\n46\t`Add` holds a write lock; `List` holds a read lock. `List` returns `[]Event{}` (not nil) so `json.Marshal` produces `[]` rather than `null`.\n47\t\n48\t### Handlers (`handlers.go`)\n49\t\n50\tBoth are constructor functions returning `http.HandlerFunc`:\n51\t\n52\t- **`PostEvent(store *EventStore) http.HandlerFunc`**\n53\t  - Decodes JSON body into a request struct `{Type, UserID, Payload}`.\n54\t  - Validates `Type` ‚àà `{\"click-mouse\", \"submit-form\"}` ‚Äî returns `400 Bad Request` otherwise.\n55\t  - Calls `store.Add`, writes the returned `Event` as JSON with status `201 Created`.\n56\t  - Returns `400` on JSON decode failure; `405 Method Not Allowed` if not POST.\n57\t\n58\t- **`GetEvents(store *EventStore) http.HandlerFunc`**\n59\t  - Calls `store.List`, writes the result as JSON with status `200 OK`.\n60\t  - Returns `405 Method Not Allowed` if not GET.\n61\t\n62\t### Routes (`routes.go`)\n63\t\n64\t```go\n65\tfunc NewRouter(store *EventStore) http.Handler\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\tRegisters `POST /events` and `GET /events` on a `http.NewServeMux()`. Method enforcement is handled inside each handler, not in the mux pattern.\n69\t\n70\t### Dependencies\n71\t\n72\t- `github.com/google/uuid` ‚Äî UUID v4 generation for event IDs.\n73\t- Standard library only otherwise (`net/http`, `encoding/json`, `sync`).\n74\t\n75\t### Testing strategy\n76\t\n77\t- `store_test.go`: verifies `Add` assigns a non-empty ID, stores the event, and `List` returns it; verifies concurrent `Add` calls do not race (run with `-race`).\n78\t- `handlers_test.go`: uses `httptest.NewRecorder` and `httptest.NewRequest`; covers 201 on valid POST, 400 on invalid type, 400 on bad JSON, 200 array on GET (empty and non-empty), and 405 on wrong method for each endpoint.\n79\t\n80\t## Documentation\n81\t\n82\t### Implementation Notes\n83\t| File | Description |\n84\t|------|-------------|\n85\t| handlers.go.md | HTTP handler constructors for the metrics service, implementing POST and GET for the /events endpoint |\n86\t| store.go.md | Thread-safe in-memory store for frontend user interaction events, with Add and List operations |\n87\t\n88\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"f4db3215-8a1a-4790-9ca5-94e57519a088","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:12:40.320Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/README.md","content":"# metrics\n\nPurpose: Describes the design of the in-memory metrics package that records and lists frontend user interaction events.\nExposes two HTTP endpoints on port 8081, implemented as a reusable `http.Handler` returned by `routes.go`.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `store.go` | `EventStore` ‚Äî thread-safe in-memory slice of `Event` records with `Add` and `List` methods |\n| `handlers.go` | `PostEvent` and `GetEvents` ‚Äî `http.HandlerFunc` factories wired to an `EventStore` |\n| `routes.go` | `NewRouter` ‚Äî assembles and returns the `http.Handler` for the metrics service |\n| `store_test.go` | Unit tests for `EventStore.Add` and `EventStore.List` |\n| `handlers_test.go` | Unit tests for `PostEvent` and `GetEvents` using `net/http/httptest` |\n\n## Overview\n\n### Data model\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    ID      string                 `json:\"id\"`\n    Type    string                 `json:\"type\"`\n    UserID  string                 `json:\"userId\"`\n    Payload map[string]interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n}\n```\n\nField names match the spec verbatim (`id`, `type`, `userId`, `payload`).\n\n### EventStore (`store.go`)\n\n```go\ntype EventStore struct {\n    mu     sync.RWMutex\n    events []Event\n}\n\nfunc NewEventStore() *EventStore\nfunc (s *EventStore) Add(e Event) Event   // caller supplies all fields except ID; Add assigns UUID and appends\nfunc (s *EventStore) List() []Event       // returns a shallow copy; never returns nil\n```\n\n`Add` holds a write lock; `List` holds a read lock. `List` returns `[]Event{}` (not nil) so `json.Marshal` produces `[]` rather than `null`.\n\n### Handlers (`handlers.go`)\n\nBoth are constructor functions returning `http.HandlerFunc`:\n\n- **`PostEvent(store *EventStore) http.HandlerFunc`**\n  - Decodes JSON body into a request struct `{Type, UserID, Payload}`.\n  - Validates `Type` ‚àà `{\"click-mouse\", \"submit-form\"}` ‚Äî returns `400 Bad Request` otherwise.\n  - Calls `store.Add`, writes the returned `Event` as JSON with status `201 Created`.\n  - Returns `400` on JSON decode failure; `405 Method Not Allowed` if not POST.\n\n- **`GetEvents(store *EventStore) http.HandlerFunc`**\n  - Calls `store.List`, writes the result as JSON with status `200 OK`.\n  - Returns `405 Method Not Allowed` if not GET.\n\n### Routes (`routes.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc NewRouter(store *EventStore) http.Handler\n```\n\nRegisters `POST /events` and `GET /events` on a `http.NewServeMux()`. Method enforcement is handled inside each handler, not in the mux pattern.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` ‚Äî UUID v4 generation for event IDs.\n- Standard library only otherwise (`net/http`, `encoding/json`, `sync`).\n\n### Testing strategy\n\n- `store_test.go`: verifies `Add` assigns a non-empty ID, stores the event, and `List` returns it; verifies concurrent `Add` calls do not race (run with `-race`).\n- `handlers_test.go`: uses `httptest.NewRecorder` and `httptest.NewRequest`; covers 201 on valid POST, 400 on invalid type, 400 on bad JSON, 200 array on GET (empty and non-empty), and 405 on wrong method for each endpoint.\n\n## Documentation\n\n### Implementation Notes\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| handlers.go.md | HTTP handler constructors for the metrics service, implementing POST and GET for the /events endpoint |\n| store.go.md | Thread-safe in-memory store for frontend user interaction events, with Add and List operations |\n\n","numLines":88,"startLine":1,"totalLines":88}}}
