{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MNbdDBADK67BuawttWVMVQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BTdqZSGWefyiPHAg6adJk6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/lifecycle/README.md","content":"# lifecycle\n\nPurpose: Provides in-memory user CRUD and token-based authentication for the IAM listener. Implements five HTTP endpoints exposed via an `*http.ServeMux` for registration by integrate-iam.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `lifecycle.go` | `UserStore`, `TokenStore`, `handler` struct, `Handler()` constructor, all five HTTP handler methods |\n| `lifecycle_test.go` | Table-driven HTTP tests for all five endpoints using `net/http/httptest` |\n\n## Overview\n\nThe package owns two in-memory stores, each protected by a `sync.RWMutex`:\n\n- **UserStore** ‚Äî two maps keyed by ID and by username, holding `{id, username, passwordHash}` records.\n- **TokenStore** ‚Äî one map keyed by opaque token string, mapping to the owning user ID.\n\nIDs and tokens are generated with `github.com/google/uuid` (v4). Passwords are hashed with `golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt` (cost 12). All response bodies are JSON; errors use `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}`.\n\n`Handler()` is the single public entry point. It constructs both stores, wires them into a private `handler` struct, and returns a `*http.ServeMux` with all five routes registered. Because the module targets Go 1.21, method-prefix patterns (`POST /users`) are not available ‚Äî the mux registers bare paths and each handler switches on `r.Method`. Path parameters for `/users/{id}` are extracted by splitting `r.URL.Path`.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` ‚Äî already in `go.mod`; used for ID and token generation\n- `golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt` ‚Äî must be added to `go.mod` (`go get golang.org/x/crypto`)\n\nSee [api.md](api.md) for the full endpoint contract.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":28782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"67844dd1-a23d-4c36-a0e4-ded206b27435"}
